# startDate

**Type**

The start date of a timespan, expressed in UNIX time, in milliseconds.

## Declaration

```swift
timestamp startDate
```

## Discussion

The start date must be earlier than the [doc://com.apple.appstoreserverapi/documentation/AppStoreServerAPI/endDate].

## Data types

- **endDate**: The end date of a timespan, expressed in UNIX time, in milliseconds.
- **notificationType**: A notification type value that App Store Server Notifications 2 uses.
- **notificationSubtype**: A notification subtype value that App Store Server Notifications 2 uses.
- **onlyFailures**: A Boolean value that indicates whether the response includes only notifications that failed to reach your server.
